	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b></b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />The 4 cycles it's talking about are from a different clock base.  The scanline is only 1 PPU cycle (1 pixel) shorter.
<br />
<br />All scanlines = 341 cycles except for the pre-render scanline, which is <em>sometimes</em> 340 (only on Odd Frames, and only if PPU is on at the appropriate time)

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


